whereas.text:
Whereas, since 2011, nearly 3,000,000 Syrian children have been forced to quit their education as
			 fighting has destroyed classrooms, left children too terrified to go to
			 school, and forced families to flee the country;

paragraph.text:
calls on the international community to assist the people of Syria, especially internally displaced
			 persons and refugees, in meeting basic needs, including access to food,
			 health care, shelter, and clean drinking water;

calls on the international community to support civilians and innocent victims of the conflict in
			 Syria, particularly women and children who are displaced and vulnerable to
			 physical and psychological exploitation;

calls on the international community to implement steps that prevent gender-based violence, and
			 assure the protection of women and girls against sexual exploitation,
			 human trafficking, and rape;

calls on the international community to continue to support neighboring countries and host
			 communities who are generously supporting refugees fleeing the conflict in
			 Syria;
